menu "breadboard: bb_timer"

config BB_TIMER_DISP_STACK
    int "Shared dispatcher task stack size (bytes)"
    default 4096
    range 2048 16384
    help
        Stack for the bb_timer_disp task that runs MODE A deferred
        work functions. mdns/cache/cJSON are safe; TLS is not (use MODE B).

config BB_TIMER_DISP_PRIORITY
    int "Shared dispatcher task priority"
    default 5
    range 1 20
    help
        FreeRTOS priority for the bb_timer_disp task. Default 5: above
        bb_pub worker (1) and bb_event_disp (5, equal), below the
        esp_timer service task (~22).

config BB_TIMER_DISP_CORE
    int "Shared dispatcher task core affinity (-1 = no affinity)"
    default -1
    range -1 1
    help
        Core to pin the bb_timer_disp task to. Default -1 (no affinity) lets
        the scheduler place it on whichever core has CPU. Without affinity,
        the prio-5 dispatcher cannot be starved on boards where core 1 runs
        a high-priority CPU-bound task (e.g. mining at prio 20). Boards that
        specifically want it off the esp_timer service core (core 0) can still
        pin it explicitly via CONFIG_BB_TIMER_DISP_CORE.

config BB_TIMER_DISP_QUEUE_DEPTH
    int "Shared dispatcher coalescing queue depth"
    default 16
    range 4 64
    help
        Depth of the internal queue between signal-only timer callbacks
        and the bb_timer_disp worker task. With coalescing, one slot per
        timer is sufficient in practice; the queue is a safety net for
        burst scenarios.

config BB_TIMER_DISP_WDT_ENABLE
    bool "Subscribe bb_timer_disp to the Task Watchdog Timer"
    default n
    depends on ESP_TASK_WDT_EN
    help
        When enabled, the shared dispatcher task (bb_timer_disp) subscribes
        to the global Task WDT at startup and feeds it on every idle timeout
        and after each work_fn returns.

        A work_fn that blocks longer than CONFIG_ESP_TASK_WDT_TIMEOUT_S
        (the global Task WDT timeout) will trigger a TWDT panic and a clean
        reboot with reset_reason task_wdt. This converts a silent WiFi-zombie
        stall into an observable reboot.

        The effective stall-to-reboot bound is CONFIG_ESP_TASK_WDT_TIMEOUT_S,
        not BB_TIMER_DISP_WDT_FEED_MS. The feed interval only controls how
        often the dispatcher feeds on idle (queue empty) ticks; it must be
        shorter than the global WDT timeout.

        Default n — opt-in; the default build is unchanged.

config BB_TIMER_DISP_WDT_FEED_MS
    int "Dispatcher WDT idle feed interval (ms)"
    default 5000
    range 1000 30000
    depends on BB_TIMER_DISP_WDT_ENABLE
    help
        How often the bb_timer_disp task feeds the Task WDT when the
        dispatch queue is empty (idle). Must be shorter than
        CONFIG_ESP_TASK_WDT_TIMEOUT_S. Default 5000 ms.

endmenu
